# Agent Module Rules

## Tool Implementation

- Every tool MUST use Ghostfolio's existing services (`PortfolioService`,
  `OrderService`, `DataProviderService`) — never call external APIs directly.
- All tool responses must be structured JSON with explicit field names.
- Always `try/catch` in every tool — return a structured error object on failure.
- Validate all tool inputs with Zod schemas.

## Safety & Compliance

- The agent must NEVER fabricate numerical data — all numbers must originate
  from tool call results.
- The agent must NEVER provide specific buy/sell investment advice.
- The agent must NEVER suggest copying any politician's trades.
- The agent must include a financial disclaimer when discussing performance data.
- The agent must include confidence scoring (`Low` / `Medium` / `High`) on every
  response.
- Congressional portfolio data is PUBLIC record — safe to discuss and analyze,
  but always framed as educational/analytical only.

## File Organization

- Agent services, tools, graph definitions → `libs/agent/src/lib/`
- API controllers / endpoints → `apps/api/src/app/agent/`
- Barrel export everything through `libs/agent/src/index.ts`

## Observability

- Wrap all LLM calls with Langfuse tracing.
- Include `traceId` in agent responses for debugging.
- Log tool invocations with input/output shapes for eval pipelines.
